rop=1\u0026amp;resize=110%2C73 110w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/law-and-order-organized-crime-5x02-1.jpg?w=600\u0026amp;h=400\u0026amp;crop=1\u0026amp;resize=285%2C190 285w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/law-and-order-organized-crime-5x02-1.jpg?w=600\u0026amp;h=400\u0026amp;crop=1\u0026amp;resize=320%2C213 320w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/law-and-order-organized-crime-5x02-1.jpg?w=600\u0026amp;h=400\u0026amp;crop=1\u0026amp;resize=640%2C427 640w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/law-and-order-organized-crime-5x02-1.jpg?w=600\u0026amp;h=400\u0026amp;crop=1\u0026amp;resize=800%2C533 800w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" fetchpriority=\"auto\" data-attachment-id=\"1235413673\" data-wp-size=\"nova_size__threebytwo_medium_cropped\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eLaw \u0026amp; Order: Organized Crime\u003c/em\u003e Season 5: Everything We Know So Far\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e“Oh, girlfriend’s coming on,” Meloni said during an interview about his show’s next season. Similarly, in May, Hargitay said it was “time now” for the characters to reunite. “This was a long time not being in each other’s universe,” she added. “That’s why we did the calls and stuff like that. But we’re excited to get back in there, get back in the ring.” \u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003ePer the season’s official synopsis, the new season will explore “the dangerous worlds of cross-border smuggling, high-tech domestic terrorism and a crime family intent on repaying Stabler for the injury he did them in Rome. As his worlds collide, Stabler will put everything on the line to protect the vulnerable and fight for justice.”\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eLaw \u0026amp; Order: Organized Crime\u003c/em\u003e will be back for Season 5 on Thursday, April 17, with its first two episodes (of 10). Episode 1 also will air on NBC that evening, at 10/9c.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePress PLAY on the video above to watch the teaser, then hit the comments with your thoughts on the latest \u003cem\u003eSVU\u003c/em\u003e/\u003cem\u003eOrganized Crime\u003c/em\u003e crossover!\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
